cs.LG, cs.SD, cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper deals with sequence modeling using recurrent neural networks and latent variables. The most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning) as the paper focuses on comparing the performance of different models on various datasets. The paper also involves natural language processing tasks, which falls under cs.CL (Computation and Language). The use of auto-regressive output distribution suggests the involvement of cs.SD (Sound) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper involves neural networks, which falls under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
